# AWS S3 Public Access Vulnerability

## What I did:

- Disabled Block Public Access settings
- Added bucket policy to allow public read access
- Made S3 objects publicly accessible

---

## Key Learnings:

- Public buckets allow anyone on the internet to access data
- Bucket policies control access permissions
- Misconfiguration can lead to data exposure

---

## Hands-on Summary:

- Disabled Block Public Access
- Applied public read policy
- Accessed object using public URL without authentication

---

## Mistakes to Avoid:

- Leaving public access enabled in production
- Granting access to "*" (everyone) without control
- Not reviewing bucket policies

---

## Security Insight:

- Public S3 buckets are a common cause of data breaches
- Sensitive data can be exposed unintentionally

